            <scopecontent>
                <p>Letters, patents, notes and treatises relating to inventors and inventions,
                    collected by Penrose Robinson Hoopes, a Philadelphia engineer. Includes
                    "Mechanical Manipulation Turning, Forging etc. Grinding, Polishing etc.," and
                    undated (c. 1860) mechanics commonplace books, The Practical Metal-Workers
                    Assistant (Philadelphia, 1851), also a Portsmouth, N.H. watchmaker's daybook,
                    1801-12.</p>
            </scopecontent>


